#: ../../N/nanotechnology.rst:5
msgid "nanotechnology"
msgstr "nanotechnology"

#: ../../N/nanotechnology.rst:7
msgid "/nan'·oh·tek·no\\`l\\@·jee/, n\\."
msgstr "/nan'·oh·tek·no\\`l\\@·jee/, 名詞"

#: ../../N/nanotechnology.rst:9
msgid ""
"A hypothetical fabrication technology in which objects are designed and "
"built with the individual specification and placement of each separate atom."
" The first unequivocal nanofabrication experiments took place in 1990, for "
"example with the deposition of individual xenon atoms on a nickel substrate "
"to spell the logo of a certain very large computer company. Nanotechnology "
"has been a hot topic in the hacker subculture ever since the term was coined"
" by K. Eric Drexler in his book *Engines of Creation* (Anchor/Doubleday, "
"ISBN 0-385-19973-2), where he predicted that nanotechnology could give rise "
"to replicating assemblers, permitting an exponential growth of productivity "
"and personal wealth (there's an authorized transcription at "
"`http://www.foresight.org/EOC/index.html "
"<http://www.foresight.org/EOC/index.html>`_). See also :ref:`blue-goo`\\, "
":ref:`gray-goo`\\, :ref:`nanobot`\\."
msgstr ""
"個々の原子それぞれを個別に指定・配置して、オブジェクトを設計・構築する仮想的な製造技術。最初の明白なナノ製造実験は1990年に行われた。たとえば、ニッケル基板上に個々のキセノン原子を堆積させて、ある非常に大きなコンピュータ会社のロゴを綴った。ナノテクノロジーは、K."
" Eric Drexlerが著書\\ *Engines of Creation*\\ (Anchor/Doubleday, ISBN "
"0-385-19973-2)でこの語を造って以来、ハッカーのサブカルチャーでホットな話題であり続けている。同書で彼は、ナノテクノロジーが自己複製する組立機を生み出し、生産性と個人の富の指数関数的成長を可能にすると予言した(\\"
" `http://www.foresight.org/EOC/index.html "
"<http://www.foresight.org/EOC/index.html>`_\\ に公認の書き起こしがある)。\\ :ref:`blue-"
"goo`\\ 、\\ :ref:`gray-goo`\\ 、\\ :ref:`nanobot`\\ も参照。"
